The paper discusses the use of knowledge maps for information retrieval, which is a core topic in the field of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the importance of interactive visualizations for exploring digital library collections, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper touches upon the use of models and user studies, which are common in the field of data mining and machine learning (cs.DL). The paper also discusses the potential of knowledge maps for cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY) and interactive visualizations for information exploration (cs.SI).
